    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Reed or bamboo pens used to apply hot wax to batik work. The hot wax is poured into a copper bowl at the tip the pen and exits through a thin needle.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
